.TH SHOREWALL-NFT 8 "2026-04-11" "shorewall-nft 0.12.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft \- nftables-native firewall compiler with Shorewall-compatible configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shorewall\-nft
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ DIRECTORY ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shorewall\-nft
is a Python implementation of the Shorewall firewall compiler that
emits native nftables rulesets instead of iptables. It is a drop\-in
replacement for Shorewall that reads the same configuration files
and produces semantically equivalent firewall behavior on modern
Linux kernels.

Configuration files live under \fI/etc/shorewall\fR (v4),
\fI/etc/shorewall6\fR (v6), or \fI/etc/shorewall46\fR (merged
dual\-stack, produced by \fBshorewall\-nft merge\-config\fR). The
merged directory takes precedence if present.

.SH LIFECYCLE COMMANDS
.TP
.B start \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Compile and apply the firewall ruleset.
.TP
.B stop
Remove all rules from the inet shorewall table.
.TP
.B restart \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Recompile and atomically replace the loaded ruleset.
.TP
.B reload \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Alias for restart (nft does atomic replace natively).
.TP
.B status
Show firewall status, chain count, rule count, and config hash drift.
.TP
.B clear
Remove all rules and load accept\-all policies.
.TP
.B save \fR[\fIFILENAME\fR]
Dump the current ruleset (like \fBnft list ruleset\fR).
.TP
.B restore \fIFILENAME\fR
Load a saved ruleset from file.
.TP
.B check \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
Compile without applying. Validates kernel capabilities.
.TP
.B compile \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR]
Compile the config to an nft script.

.SH NFT\-NATIVE EXTENSIONS
.TP
.B debug \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR \fIFILTER\fR]
Temporarily load a debug\-annotated ruleset with per\-rule counters
and source\-location comments. Ctrl+C restores the original.
.TP
.B trace \fR[\fB\-\-netns\fR \fINS\fR]
Run \fBnft monitor trace\fR. Packets marked with
\fBmeta nftrace set 1\fR produce trace events showing the exact rule
that made the verdict.
.TP
.B verify \fIDIRECTORY\fR \fB\-\-iptables\fR \fIDUMP\fR
Semantic comparison between the compiled output and an
\fBiptables\-save\fR baseline (triangle verifier).
.TP
.B simulate \fIDIRECTORY\fR \fB\-\-iptables\fR \fIDUMP\fR
Packet\-level verification in 3 network namespaces using scapy.
.TP
.B lookup \fIIP\fR
Query all configured plugins for metadata about an IP.
.TP
.B enrich \fR[\fIDIRECTORY\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
Rewrite ?COMMENT blocks in\-place with plugin annotations.
.TP
.B merge\-config \fIV4\fR \fR[\fIV6\fR] [\fB\-o\fR \fIOUT\fR] [\fB\-\-guided\fR]
Merge /etc/shorewall and /etc/shorewall6 into a unified
/etc/shorewall46 directory.
.TP
.B plugins list
Show loaded plugins with their priorities.

.SH CONFIG DIRECTORY OVERRIDE FLAGS
All commands that take a directory accept these mutually exclusive
overrides:
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config\-dir " \fIDIR\fR"
Explicit merged config directory (overrides /etc/shorewall46 default).
.TP
.BI \-\-config\-dir4 " DIR"
Explicit IPv4 config directory.
.TP
.BI \-\-config6\-dir " DIR"
Explicit IPv6 config directory (combine with \-\-config\-dir4 for
explicit dual mode).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-v4
Disable auto\-detection of a v4 sibling (for v6\-only mode).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-v6
Disable auto\-detection of a v6 sibling (for v4\-only mode).

The six supported modes are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Default: \fBshorewall\-nft start\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Merged: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-c /srv/merged\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Dual auto\-sibling: \fBshorewall\-nft start /srv/v4\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Dual explicit: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config\-dir4 /srv/v4 \-\-config6\-dir /srv/v6\fR
.IP \(bu 2
v4\-only: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config\-dir4 /srv/v4 \-\-no\-auto\-v6\fR
.IP \(bu 2
v6\-only: \fBshorewall\-nft start \-\-config6\-dir /srv/v6 \-\-no\-auto\-v4\fR
.RE

.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-netns " \fINAMESPACE\fR"
Target a Linux network namespace (requires
\fB/usr/local/bin/run\-netns\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help for the command and exit.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/
Legacy IPv4 Shorewall config.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall6/
Legacy IPv6 Shorewall config.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall46/
Merged dual\-stack config (takes precedence).
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/plugins.conf
Plugin registry (TOML).
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/plugins/*.toml
Per\-plugin configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/plugins/netbox\-cache.json
Netbox plugin local cache (may contain sensitive data).

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PYTHONPATH
Standard Python module search path. Tests and dev installs require
the project root on PYTHONPATH.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Compile error, verification failure, or runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Argument parsing or usage error.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the firewall using the default config directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
shorewall-nft start
.fi
.RE
.PP
Debug a specific traffic flow in a netns:
.PP
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft debug /etc/shorewall \\
    \-\-netns fw \\
    \-\-trace 'ip saddr 192.168.1.100'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Merge dual\-stack config and verify against iptables baseline:
.PP
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft merge\-config /etc/shorewall /etc/shorewall6
shorewall\-nft verify --iptables /tmp/iptables\-save.txt
.fi
.RE
.PP
Plugin lookup with machine\-readable output:
.PP
.RS
.nf
shorewall\-nft lookup 203.0.113.65 --json
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nft (8),
.BR iptables (8),
.BR shorewall (8),
.BR ip-netns (8)

